### Assessing the Team

After doing the valuation, you have to make sure the team is the right one.

Evaluating a founder can be just as, if not more, important as the startup itself.

The three most important features of the team/founder should be: 

1. Character
2. Confidence
3. Coach-ability

Overall look for: Sum of their parts (how do they complement one another? Do they fill all of the necessary requirements? 
Are all of the required skills accounted for? 

Read these quick tips to help you [**identify a founder worth investing in.**](https://republic.co/blog/investor-education/how-to-evaluate-startup-founders)


- Evaluate these three startups' teams and determine which team is best placed to build their startup:

[**Mattermark Pitch Deck](https://www.slideshare.net/DanielleMorrill/mattermark-2nd-final-series-a-deck)** 

[**Square Pitch Deck**](https://www.slideshare.net/pitchenvy/square-pitch-deck)

[**Buzzfeed Pitch Deck**](https://www.slideshare.net/TechInAsiaID/buzzfeed-pitch-deck)

- List further questions you would ask each team

Recommend Watch: [**How to Build and Manage Teams**](https://www.ycombinator.com/library/7g-how-to-build-and-manage-teams-sus-2017)
